003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eHardware isn\u0026#39;t the only factor\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-boost-mobile-hotspot-speed/\" title=\"My 6 Handy Tips for Boosting Your Mobile Hotspot Speeds\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tMy 6 Handy Tips for Boosting Your Mobile Hotspot Speeds\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eBoost your mobile hotspot speeds with these easy-to-implement tips and tricks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"hunting-down-your-home-rsquo-s-sweet-spot\"\u003e\n                        Hunting Down Your Homeâ€™s Sweet Spot\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eOf these three metrics, RSRP is the one you can directly influence by repositioning your phone. I discovered that placing my phone on a kitchen windowsill, just a meter above the floor, boosted my RSRP from around â€“120â€¯dBm to nearly â€“80â€¯dBm.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eBecause RSRQ and SINR depend on network load and ambient interference, they often fluctuate with the time of day and how many neighbors are streaming video. If those numbers dip too low, your only options are switching to a less congested bandâ€”a \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/iphone-vs-android-missing-features/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003efeature that\u0026#39;s available on Android but not on iOS\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe band information is handy if your phone lets you manually choose one. For example, midâ€‘band around 2.6â€¯GHz offers more capacity but struggles with indoor penetration, while lower bands near 800â€¯MHz travel through walls more easily.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Amir Bohlooli \\/ MakeUseOf\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                             \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2000\" height=\"1148\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"iPhone slapped on a window\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/iphone-slapped-on-a-window.jpg\"/\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eAmir Bohlooli / MakeUseOf\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e The truth is, RSRP is the only metric you can consistently influence inside your home. RSRQ and SINR depend on network congestion, time of day, and your neighbor\u0026#39;s habits. So, bring up the signal metrics, walk around your house, and hunt down that sweet spot. For me, it was the windowsill in the kitchen. I have a suction mount on my case, which lets me slap my phone on the window.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\n\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_26\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n\n        \n            \u003cp\u003eDonâ€™t ignore your Wi-Fi. Even if your phone is perfectly placed for cell signal, your PC needs to reach its hotspot too. Find a compromise.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIâ€™ve also noticed that my Nothing Phone 1 consistently gets better signal and faster speeds than my iPhone 16 Pro, even though both use the same carrier. In areas where the Nothing Phone shows 5G, the iPhone often drops to LTE.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThat tells me one of two things: either the Nothing Phone has a better modem, or itâ€™s simply more compatible with the network bands my carrier uses. Either way, if you want to squeeze out the best performance, use the better device as your hotspot.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"8855-4d62-85b3b52bcbcd\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/use-mobile-hotspot-without-exceeding-data-cap/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                             \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1680\" height=\"840\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"hand holding an Android phone showing the Mobile Hotspot feature in front of a computer monitor\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/hand-holding-an-android-phone-showing-the-mobile-hotspot-feature-in-front-of-a-computer-monitor.jpg\"/\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWalls, windows, furniture, and appliances all conspire to sap signal strength, even when you live next to a cell tower. Iâ€™ve experienced this firsthand as Iâ€™ve leaned on mobile data more during power outages in my area. A tiny shift in my apartment, sometimes mere inches, would send my download speed and connection stability swinging wildly.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eYour house has a cell signal sweet spot, whether you know it or not. A two-minute walk with Field Test Mode open can mean the difference between a flaky connection and a rock-solid hotspot.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
